---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import '../styles/home.css';
import '../styles/legal.css';

import Nav from '../components/home/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/home/Footer.astro';

// Copy is verbatim from the vault: 02 Platform/02 Privacy Policy & Guardian
// Consent (Draft), Part 1. The combined legal review before launch is a
// tracked owner task; wording changes land here when it returns. The meta
// description is an unaltered sentence from that note's "Who we are" section.
const description =
  'This policy explains what personal information we collect, why, who we share it with, and the choices and rights you have.';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy - Women in Aviation Middle East"
  description={description}
  path="/privacy/"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="Women in Aviation Middle East" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Privacy Policy" />
    <meta property="og:description" content={description} />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://www.waiorg.me/assets/share-card.png" />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://www.waiorg.me/assets/share-card.png" />
  </Fragment>

  <span class="top-sentinel" id="topSentinel" aria-hidden="true"></span>

  <Nav />

  <main id="main">
    <span id="top"></span>

    <header class="legal-hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          This policy explains what personal information we collect, why, who we
          share it with, and the choices and rights you have.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="legal-body">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="legal-inner">
          <h2>Who we are</h2>
          <p>
            Women in Aviation Middle East (WAI-ME) is a recognised chapter of Women in
            Aviation International, hosted by the Emirates Aerosports Federation, which
            provides our registered address: c/o Emirates Aerosports Federation, Skydive
            HQ, Dubai, United Arab Emirates. This policy explains what personal
            information we collect, why, who we share it with, and the choices and
            rights you have. Questions or requests:
            <a href="mailto:support@waiorg.me">support@waiorg.me</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our members come from more than 40 countries, so we follow both the
            <strong>UAE Personal Data Protection Law (PDPL)</strong> and, where it
            applies, the <strong>EU/UK General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)</strong>.
          </p>

          <h2>What we collect</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>When you join:</strong> your name, email, date of birth, country, gender, and your stage in aviation (for example student, early-career, or established professional). If you are under 18, we also collect a parent or guardian's name and email so they can confirm your membership.</li>
            <li><strong>If your record moved over from our earlier member list:</strong> it may also include a mobile number and your previous role or company, exactly as you gave them to us before.</li>
            <li><strong>In your profile:</strong> certifications and licences, experience, role or specialisation, education, a short bio or personal statement, and, if you choose, a CV.</li>
            <li><strong>When you take part:</strong> events you attend, certificates you earn, workshops you join, and contributions you make in the community.</li>
            <li><strong>Automatically:</strong> basic, privacy-friendly website analytics (we use Cloudflare Web Analytics, which does not track you across other sites or use advertising cookies).</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Why we use it, and our lawful basis</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>To run your membership:</strong> your account, profile, certificates, and event participation. <em>Basis: performance of our agreement with you / legitimate interest.</em></li>
            <li><strong>To send you news and updates by email:</strong> only if you opt in. <em>Basis: your consent (you can withdraw it any time).</em></li>
            <li><strong>To make your profile searchable by our corporate partners</strong> (the talent pipeline), only if you switch this on. <em>Basis: your separate, explicit, revocable consent.</em></li>
            <li><strong>To consider you for scholarships and opportunities</strong> you apply for. <em>Basis: your request and consent.</em></li>
            <li><strong>To keep the community safe:</strong> handling code-of-conduct and safeguarding matters. <em>Basis: legitimate interest and legal obligation.</em></li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Your choices</h2>
          <p>Three separate, clearly-labelled choices, not one blanket tick:</p>
          <ol>
            <li><strong>Membership terms and this privacy policy:</strong> required to join.</li>
            <li><strong>Marketing and update emails:</strong> optional, and you can turn them off any time.</li>
            <li><strong>Make my profile searchable by corporate partners:</strong> optional, off unless you turn it on, and reversible at any time.</li>
          </ol>
          <p>We record which version of each you agreed to, and when.</p>

          <h2>Who we share it with</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Corporate partners:</strong> only the profiles of members who switched on the talent-pipeline option, and only so partners can offer jobs, internships, mentorship, and scholarships. Partners must use this information <strong>only</strong> for that purpose, must not keep it longer than needed, and must not pass it on or sell it.</li>
            <li><strong>Scholarship partners:</strong> a shortlist of applicants for a specific scholarship you applied for, under the same use-only-for-this-purpose rule.</li>
            <li><strong>Service providers who run our systems for us:</strong> our database (Convex), our email senders (Resend and EmailOctopus), our official support mailbox (Zoho Mail), and our website infrastructure (Cloudflare). They process data on our instructions under data-protection agreements. You can ask us at any time where your data is stored.</li>
            <li>We do <strong>not</strong> sell your personal information to anyone, ever.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Sending data across borders</h2>
          <p>
            Some of our service providers store data outside your country. Where that
            happens, we rely on the providers' standard data-protection terms so
            transfers are handled lawfully, and you can ask us at any time where your
            data is stored.
          </p>

          <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
          <p>
            We keep your membership record while you are a member. If an account becomes
            inactive, we flag it as dormant after about three years rather than deleting
            it automatically, so you can return. <strong>If you ask us to delete your
            data, we delete it (or irreversibly anonymise it), keeping only the minimum
            the law requires.</strong> Safeguarding records are kept longer, as
            safeguarding good practice and law require. (Full rules: our internal
            data-retention policy.)
          </p>

          <h2>Your rights</h2>
          <p>
            You can ask us to: see the data we hold about you; correct it; delete it;
            stop sending you marketing; or turn off partner searchability. You can also
            withdraw any consent you gave, and complain to a data-protection authority.
            To exercise any of these, email
            <a href="mailto:support@waiorg.me">support@waiorg.me</a>. We respond within
            the timeframes the law sets. (As the member area grows, these options will
            also appear there directly.)
          </p>

          <h2>Keeping your data safe</h2>
          <p>
            We protect your data with access controls, secure providers, and a small,
            named admin team. If a data breach ever affected your information, we follow
            a set plan to contain it, assess it, and notify you and the relevant
            authority within the legal timeframes (72 hours under GDPR, and as PDPL
            requires).
          </p>

          <h2>Children and young members</h2>
          <p>
            Members must be at least 13. Members under 18 join with a parent or
            guardian's consent and go into a protected setting with extra safeguards,
            see <a href="/safeguarding">Safeguarding of Members Under 18</a>. We do not
            knowingly sign up anyone under 13 as their own member.
          </p>

          <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
          <p>
            If we change this policy, we update the date below and, for important
            changes, tell members directly.
          </p>

          <p class="updated">
            Last updated: 2 July 2026 · Contact:
            <a href="mailto:support@waiorg.me">support@waiorg.me</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />

  <script src="../scripts/home-motion.js"></script>
</Base>
